Premier League club, West Bromwich Albion, on Wednesday sacked its manager, Slaven Bilić following the clubs 1-1 draw with Manchester City on Tuesday night. West Brom disclosed this in a statement via its website on Wednesday afternoon. The statement read: “West Bromwich Albion have today parted company with Head Coach Slaven Bilić. “Assistant Coaches, Dean Računica and Danilo Butorović, and First Team Coach Julian Dicks have also left the club with immediate effect. “Albion would like to thank Slaven and his coaching staff for their efforts in achieving promotion last season and wishes them all well in the future. “The club will make no further comment at this time.” West Brom is currently on the 19th position on the Premier League table with seven points after 13 matches.